  "text": "For demodulation of the ASK signals, an ordinary envelope detector can be used. However, this method is sensitive to the distance between the two coils. Instead, we count the number of RF cycles for a given burst [CITATION_1] , which allows easy discrimination among 0, 1, or EOF bits. We found that this method is more reliable and far less sensitive to the coil-to-coil distance than the envelope detection method.",
